    <p>This service is managed by the Ministry of Justice (MOJ). MOJ is the data controller for the personal information we hold.</p>
    <p>MOJ collects and processes personal data so that it can safely and securely provide answers to correspondence.</p>

    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">About personal information</h3>
    <p>Personal data is information about you as an individual. It can be your name, address or telephone number.</p>
    <p>We know how important it is to protect your privacy and to comply with data protection laws. We will keep your personal data safe and will only disclose it where it is lawful to do so, or with your consent.</p>

    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Types of personal data we process</h3>
    <p>We only process personal data that is relevant for the services we are providing to you. This includes your question, query, feedback and email address. We also collect site-usage information which allows us to see how the service is being used in order to allow us to improve it. This information does not contain any personal data. It includes:</p>

    <%= govuk_list [
        "your IP address, and details of which version of web browser you used",
        "information on how you use the site, using cookies and page tagging techniques to help us improve the website"
      ], type: "bullet"
    %>

    <p>This helps us to:</p>
    <%= govuk_list [
        "improve the site by monitoring how you use it",
        "respond to any feedback you send us, if you’ve asked us to",
        "provide you with information about local services if you want it"
      ], type: "bullet"
    %>

    <p>We can’t personally identify you using your site usage data.</p>

    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Purpose of processing and the lawful basis for the process</h3>
    <p>We collect personal data to enable us to tailor and respond to your correspondence accordingly.</p>

    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Who the information may be shared with</h3>
    <p>We do not share your information with anyone else.</p>

    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Details of transfers to third country and safeguards</h3>
    <p>All data collected by this service is stored within the European Economic Area (EEA). However, due to the global nature of the internet, the data sent to and from the database may transit through countries outside of the EEA. Data is not stored in a non-EEA country. Any transfers made will be in full compliance with all aspects of the data protection law.</p>

    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">How long we keep data</h3>
    <p>In the case of Freedom of Information (FOI) requests, data is retained for three years after the last action in accordance with FOI retention policy.</p>
    <p>In the case of Information Commissioner Reviews, data is destroyed after 5 years from last action.</p>
    <p>For all other requests, data is retained for two years after the last action.</p>

